gomodel:SYNGO_1763  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2025-04-10: GO:0061077 replaced by GO:0006457" , "Rationale: Figure 6 shows that SGT when complimented with CSP-alpha and Hsc-70 acts against the protein misfolding (aggregation state) of SNAP-25. Supporting the formation of a trimeric complex in regulation of SNAP-25's half life.\n\n29/01/2018 Pim\n- Although the data in Fig.6 show the direct role of SGT-alpha (small glutamine-rich tetratricopeptide repeat protein alpha) in the chaperoning in a cell free system. The relevance for and occurence in vivo is suggested by the IP data in Fig.5. Here SNAP-25 IP resulted in selective CSPα, Hsc70 and SGT or SNARE proteins pulldown from brain homogenates.\n- Effects on synaptic transmission is not shown in these or other data since the CSP KO is lethal. A role in SV exocytosis is proposed by the authors. This may be a reasonable inference, but I decided not to annotate to term 'regulation of synaptic vesicle exocytosis'.. Experimental description: Inferred from isolation of the original cDNA for SGT-alpha in PMID:11580898" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2025-04-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1763" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

